FBIS4-13124 "drnes074_c_94015" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 16 Apr 1994 Egypt `Extremists' Handed Over in Asyut `Extremists' Handed Over in Asyut NC1604161494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1545 GMT 16 Apr 94 NC1604161494 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo, 16 Apr (MENA)--Asyut Governor Samih al-Sa'id has announced that popular committees this morning handed over to the Asyut security service 16 extremists who repented after being misled by fugitive extremist leaders who deceived them into believing that they were fighting for religion. The governor added that the security services will release these persons after authenticating their repentance. He affirmed that current popular efforts all over the governorate will help wipe out fugitive terrorists and those involved in murder, sabotage, and hostile activities now that the help they used to receive from these people has stopped.
